    # Check if this key was already processed
    existing = order_log.get(idempotency_key)
    if existing:
        return json.dumps({'success': True, 'data': existing, 'idempotent': True,
                           'message': 'Returning existing order (duplicate request)'})

    # Process new order
    order = process_order(product_id, quantity)
    order_log[idempotency_key] = order
    return json.dumps({'success': True, 'data': order, 'idempotent': False})
```
The idempotency_key (e.g., session_id + step_number) ensures that if the agent retries the call after a network error, it gets the original order back rather than creating a duplicate.
